<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ861218-0088 </DOCNO><HL> Brooklyn Union IncreasesDividend to $1.66 a Share</HL><DD> 12/18/86</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> BUDIVIDENDS (DIV)TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> NEW YORK  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Brooklyn Union Gas Co., a natural gas distribution company, increased its common-stock dividend four cents a share to $1.66 a share, payable Feb. 1 to stock of record Jan. 5.    The Brooklyn, N.Y.-based company also told securities analysts here that it is on the lookout to acquire gas distribution companies in the Northeast.    Elwin S. Larson, president and chief executive officer, said Brooklyn Union isn't currently negotiating with any company. He also said the company's longstanding bid to acquire the gas unit of Long Island Lighting Co. is still on the table, though Lilco continues to oppose such a transaction. </TEXT></DOC>